Preheat your oven to 220°C and bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with a pinch of @salt{} for the potatoes. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @chicken thigh{260%g}(diced) and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden all over, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Add both to the #pot{} of boiling water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through them, ~{10-12%minutes}. When cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot, off the heat.

Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways then thinly slice widthways. Stir into the chicken. Pick the @sage{15%g} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Add to the pot, along with the @water{100%ml} (see ingredients for amount) and @chicken stock powder{1/2}. Stir to dissolve the stock powder then bring to the boil, lower the heat and simmer until reduced by half, ~{5-8%minutes}. Trim the @green beans{150}.

Stir the @apple and sage jelly{1/2} and @creme fraiche{100%g} into the chicken.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Bring to the boil then remove the pot from the heat. Pour the mixture into an #ovenproof dish{} and set aside. Mash the potato with a #potato masher{}, adding a knob of @?butter{} if you have any. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Spread the mash over the chicken filling. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g} over the top then bake on the top shelf of your #oven{} until golden and bubbly, ~{10-15%minutes}. Meanwhile, rinse and refill the #potato pan{} with water and bring to the boil. Add the green beans to the boiling water and cook until just tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Drain in the colander and return to the pot, with the #lid{} on, to keep warm.

Serve the creamy chicken and leek pie with some green beans alongside. Enjoy!